# INCIDENTS — {{project_name}}

Append-only log of incidents and lessons learned. Latest at the top.

> **Why this file exists**: when something breaks, write it down. The 5th time you write "X failed because of Y", you stop forgetting. Most valuable doc category over a 5-year horizon.

---

## How to add an entry

Format per incident:

```markdown
## YYYY-MM-DD — Short title

**What broke**: One paragraph describing the user-visible symptom.

**Root cause**: What was actually wrong. Often different from what it first looked like.

**What fixed it**: The change that resolved the incident. Link to commit / PR if applicable.

**What changed to prevent recurrence**: Tests added, monitoring added, doc updates, refactors. If "nothing", say so explicitly — not every incident requires preventive work.

**Time to detect / time to mitigate**: Optional, useful for ops-shaped projects.
```

Be honest about misdiagnoses. The value of this file is the trail, not the heroics.

